The complex solution $\vec{\mathbf{z}}(t)$ that we found in
{(a)}
and
{(b)}
is

\begin{align*}
\vec{\mathbf{z}}(t) &= e^{-t}e^{2ti}\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -i \end{pmatrix} \\
&= e^{-t}(\cos 2t + i\sin 2t)\begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ -i \end{pmatrix} \\
&= e^{-t}\begin{pmatrix}\cos 2t \\ \sin 2t\end{pmatrix} + ie^{-t}\begin{pmatrix} \sin 2t \\ -\cos 2t\end{pmatrix}
\end{align*}

From this we can read off the real-valued form as

\begin{align*}
\vec{\mathbf{x}}(t) = C_1 e^{-t}\begin{pmatrix}\cos 2t \\ \sin 2t\end{pmatrix} + C_2 e^{-t}\begin{pmatrix} \sin 2t \\ -\cos 2t\end{pmatrix}
\end{align*}

